25|$|Significant {{changes in}} Byzantine art {{coincided with the}} reign of Justinian I (527–565). Justinian devoted much of his reign to reconquering Italy, North Africa and Spain. He also laid the {{foundations}} <b>of</b> the imperial <b>absolutism</b> <b>of</b> the Byzantine state, codifying its laws and imposing his religious views on all his subjects by law.|$|R
